+                     * deliberately writes -1 into every CLUSTER/
+                     * CLUSTER_WEIGHT track's own `cluster` field for this
+                     * same reason). An embedded HSF_MOTION legitimately
+                     * containing a CLUSTER track (the storybook page-turn
+                     * model does -- REL/bootDll/opening.c's own
+                     * Hu3DMotionClusterSpeedSet(OpeningMdlId[1], 0, ...)
+                     * call confirms it) would otherwise index a NULL array
+                     * here every single frame its motion runs -- a genuine,
+                     * immediate access violation, not a theoretical one.
+                     * Bounds-checked defensively; a future milestone
+                     * implementing real cluster data closes this gap by
+                     * making the condition always true, not by removing
+                     * the check. */
+                    if (trackP->cluster >= 0 && trackP->cluster < hsf->clusterNum) {
+                        clusterP = &hsf->cluster[trackP->cluster];
+                        clusterP->index = GetClusterCurve(trackP, time);
+                    }
@@ -895,2 +944,7 @@
